HEADWORD: Homopolic
<hw>Ho`mo*pol"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Homo-</ets>
+ <ets>pole</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>In promorphology,
pertaining to or exhibiting that kind of organic form, in which the
stereometric ground form is a pyramid, with <xex>similar poles</xex>.
See <er>Promorphology</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

